channel.title: Port forwarding?
channel.description:
Hi all.
I've got a router, a Thompson SpeedTouch 510.
Now I'm having a rs2 server and want to get it online, so i think i must port forward port 43594. But how do I do this? So I go to PortForward.com. ([URL=http://portforward.com/english/routers/port_forwarding/Thomson-Alcatel/SpeedTouch510v4.0/SpeedTouch510v4.0index.htm]CLICK[/URL]) But I don't understand what I got to do, as soon as I get to the NAPT page I dont understand what to do; what do I have to fill in THESE ([URL=http://portforward.com/english/routers/port_forwarding/Thomson-Alcatel/SpeedTouch510v4.0/SpeedTouch510v4.03.jpg]CLICK[/URL]) fields? So what i must know:
Inside IP, Inside Port, Outside IP and Outside Port.
Thanks in advance.

item.title: Port forwarding?
item.dc:creator: @masonw masonw
item.description:
@masonw wrote:

Just change the two port boxes to the port you want, I think that should work.
